snippet: The town of Pilger sustained serious damage, with the county sheriff estimating that 50 to 75 percent of it was heavily damaged or destroyed.
abstract: Tornadoes rip through northeastern Nebraska, killing at least one person and injuring 16 others; town of Pilger sustains serious damage, with county sheriff estimating that 50 to 75 percent of it is heavily damaged or destroyed.
lead_paragraph: The town of Pilger sustained serious damage, with the county sheriff estimating that 50 to 75 percent of it was heavily damaged or destroyed.

headline.main: Deadly Tornadoes Sweep Across Northeast Nebraska
